Sub-Query
A subquery is also called an inner query or inner select while the statement containing a subquery is also called an outer query or outer select.

Rules:- 
Subqueries must be enclosed within parentheses.
You can use the comparison operators, such as >,<, or=, IN,ANY or ALL
An Order By command cannot be used in a sub-query.

Types of Sub Queries
1. Single row subquery  (Returns zero or one row)
2. Multiple row subquery (Returns one or more rows)
3. Correlated sub-queries (The sub-query depends on the outer query for its values) 
